                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "img": "images/pictures/about-texts-image-1.png",
                    "faIcon": "",
                    "faIconColors": {"bg": "", "fill": ""},
                    "locales": {
                        "en": {
                            "text": "I’m a [[Computer Science]] student at the University of Victoria, graduating in summer 2026, with [[16 months of full-stack development experience]] through two co-op positions. During my most recent co-op, I developed a strong interest in [[UI/UX and front-end development]]. I enjoy combining analytical problem-solving with creativity and seeing an idea move from an initial design to a real, interactive product. This has drawn me toward areas such as web development, interactive applications, and game development.<p><p>I’ve always been drawn to games, puzzles, and systems with clear rules that can be explored through different strategies—an interest that eventually helped lead me to software development. Outside of coding, I’m usually hiking, biking, camping, weightlifting, or discovering a new beach or lake around Vancouver Island with my partner. I’m currently based in Victoria, BC."
                        }
                    }
                }
            ]
        },

